    "description": "<p>This dataset contains information about publicly accessible bathrooms located across Boston. A variety of information about each location is included, such as the source of the information and whether it has been independently verified. The data was compiled by stakeholders in the Planning Department, Age Strong Commission (ASC), and Boston Centers for Youth and Families (BCYF), with support from the Downtown Boston Alliance (DBA).&nbsp;</p><p>The data is updated daily from a Google Sheet managed by the Analytics team in the Department of Innovation and Technology (DoIT).</p><p>Please note, this dataset aggregates data from multiple sources and is more robust. Therefore, this feature layer is set to replace the <a target='_blank' href='https://boston.maps.arcgis.com/home/item.html?id=52425f2197bd4336bc7b4e9be2bc0b0c' rel='nofollow ugc noopener noreferrer'>“public_bathrooms”</a> dataset developed by the Age Strong Commission in the coming months.</p>",
    "tags": [
      "Bathroom",
      "Public",
      "Restroom"
    ],
    "snippet": "Publicly accessible bathrooms across Boston. This dataset is automatically updated from a Google Sheet.",
